and we have $10$ digits and i just want to have first digit like choose from $4$ digits
and for second digit i just choose from only $9$ digit , 
and for third i  just choose from only $8$ digits.
So total ways for choose leats is
\begin{align} 5*4*3*4*3*2&=720 \\ 4*9*8&=288 \\ & 720*288=207360      \end{align}
But this solution is wrong , from where i miss out ? This is my question

It must be assumed that license plates are in every place.
So the answer to your question is:
\begin{align*}
    \begin{array}{c|c}
  \text{Vowels} &\text{Months}\\
  \hline
  5     & 4 \\
    4   & 4 \\
    3   & 4 \\
    2   & 4 \\
    1   & 4 \\
    \end{array}
\end{align*}
So:
\begin{align*}
    \begin{array}{c|c}
  \text{Vowels} &\text{Months}\\
  \hline
  5! & 4^3 \\
  4! &&   \\
  3! &&   \\
  \end{array}
\end{align*}
Hence:
\begin{align*}
    5! \cdot 4^3 \cdot 1 \cdot 4^3 \cdot 1 \cdot 4^3 = 276480
\end{align*}
翅=addition rule is used. The last  number in the multiplication must be $4^3$ because you never abd used them.

